Business Brief -- Bernard Chaus Inc.:
   Apparel Maker Posts Profit
   For Fiscal Second Quarter
The company said its Chaus Sport and Ms. Chaus Dress
divisions showed improvement, and noted that the number of
garments sold rose 21% in the quarter, and more merchandise
was sold at regular prices. Lower manufacturing costs
permitted the company to lower the average prices of
merchandise without resorting to sales, the company said.
   For the first half, net income was $1.6 million, or nine
cents a share, compared with a loss of $4 million, or 22
cents a share, a year earlier. Sales rose 8.9% to $126
million from $115.6 million.